name: INSECURITY IN SECURITY
description: INSECURITY IN SECURITY is a perfect example of words (INSECURITY & SECURITY) that are opposites outside of this context, and yet said in succession of each other with the word "IN" inbetween creates a contradictory paradigm. How can someone or something be insecure when there is security? What kind of security breathes life into insecurity? Does the security make someone insecure? What a paradoxical conundrum to be in. Is this a bizarre coincidence that this happens? That's for you, the reader, to decide. I'm just a zookeeper giving you the tour of wild words in the wilderness of the WYSIWYG (What You See Is What You Get) wonderland. This is the English language; it's incredible and has almost a malleable quality to it.
